# Docker-only development

Applies to: entire repo

## Rule

All toolchain commands (`npm install`, `npm run build`, `npm test`, `npm run lint`, `npm run check`) **must run inside Docker**, not on the host.

Use:

```bash
make setup    # first time
make check
make build
make dev
```

Or `docker compose run --rm dev <command>`.

## Exceptions

- Chrome manual smoke on the host (`chrome://extensions` → load `dist/`)
- Editing source files on the host (bind-mounted into container)

